FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Carmine Sterrantino]]|other=at [[Novara Calcio|Novara]] until 30 June 2020}}<ref name=\"giovanibianconeri.it\"/>\n{{Fs end}}\n\n==Coaching staff==\n[[File:Sarri 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Maurizio Sarri]] is the current head coach of the club]]\n{{updated|10 July 2019}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2019/the-juventus-first-team-staff-for-2019-20.php|title=The Juventus First Team staff for 2019/20|date=10 July 2019|website=Juventus.com|access-date=10 July 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" |Coaching\n|-\n|Head Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Maurizio Sarri]]\n|-\n|Assistant Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Giovanni Martusciello]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |First Team Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Marco Ianni\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Gianni Picchioni\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Loris Beoni\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Goalkeeping Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Claudio Filippi\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Massimo Nenci\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Fitness\n|-\n|Head of Fitness\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Daniele Tognaccini\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |Fitness Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Andrea Pertusio\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Davide Losi\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Enrico Maffei\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Duccio Ferrari Bravo\n|-\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Davide Ranzato\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Sport Science\n|-\n|Head of Sport Science\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Roberto Sassi\n|-\n|Sport Science Specialist and Fitness Coach\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Antonio Gualtieri\n|-\n|Sport Science Officer\n|{{Flagicon|IRE}} Darragh Connolly\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Medical\n|-\n|Head of Medical\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Luca Stefanini\n|-\n|Head of First Team Medical\n|{{Flagicon|GRE}} Nikos Tzouroudis\n|-\n|First Team Medic\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Marco Freschi\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Match Analysis\n|-\n|Head of Match Analysis\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Riccardo Scirea\n|-\n|Match Analyst\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Domenico Vernamonte\n|-\n|Match Analyst\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} Giuseppe Maiuri\n|}\n\n== Chairmen history ==\n{{see also|List of Juventus F.C. chairmen}}\nJuventus have had numerous chairmen ({{lang-it|presidenti|lit=presidents}} or {{lang-it|presidenti del consiglio di amministrazione|lit=chairmen of the board of directors}}) over the course of their history, some of which have been the owners of the club, others have been corporate managers that were nominated by the owners. On top of chairmen, there were several living former chairmen, that were nominated as the honorary chairmen ({{lang-it|Presidenti Onorari|lit=honorary presidents}}).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juworld.net/storia-presidenti-della-juventus.asp|title=List of Juventus F.C. Presidents|work=Juworld.net|language=Italian|accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref>\n{|\n|-\n|width=\"10\"|\n|valign=\"top\"|\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!Name\n!Years\n|-\n|align=left|[[Eugenio Canfari]]\n|align=left|1897\u20131898\n|-\n|align=left|[[Enrico Canfari]]\n|align=left|1898\u20131901\n|-\n|align=left|Carlo Favale\n|align=left|1901\u20131902\n|-\n|align=left|Giacomo Parvopassu\n|align=left|1903\u20131904\n|-\n|align=left|[[Alfred Dick (entrepreneur)|Alfred Dick]]\n|align=left|1905\u20131906\n|-\n|align=left|[[Carlo Vittorio Varetti]]\n|align=left|1907\u20131910\n|-\n|align=left|Attilio Ubertalli\n|align=left|1911\u20131912\n|-\n|align=left|Giuseppe Hess\n|align=left|1913\u20131915\n|-\n|align=left|Gioacchino Armano, Fernando Nizza, Sandro Zambelli{{efn|Presidential Committee of War.}}\n|align=left|1915\u20131918\n|-\n|align=left|Corrado Corradini\n|align=left|1919\u20131920\n|-\n|align=left|Gino Olivetti\n|align=left|1920\u20131923\n|-\n|align=left|[[Edoardo Agnelli (industrialist)|Edoardo Agnelli]]\n|align=left|1923\u20131935\n|-\n|align=left|Giovanni Mazzonis\n|align=left|1935\u20131936\n|}\n|width=\"30\"|\n|valign=\"top\"|\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!Name\n!Years\n|-\n|align=left|Emilio de la Forest de Divonne\n|align=left|1936\u20131941\n|-\n|align=left|Pietro Dusio\n|align=left|1941\u20131947\n|-\n|ali